cexp 0.1
========

This is a very simple PHP module that implements a couple of useful functions (IMHO).
These are ifnull() and ifempty(), copying funcionality from the MySQL equivalent ones.


Usage
=====

    ifnull($value, $value_if_null);

    Test the expression $value, if it is NULL returns the value of $value_if_null,
    if it is NOT NULL returns the value $value.

    ifempty($value, $value_if_empty);

    Test the expression $value, if it is EMPTY returns the value of $value_if_empty,
    if it is NOT EMPTY returns the value $value.

    Consider EMPTY as the value returned by the PHP function empty().


Building and installing
=======================

Run this commands from the root directory:

$ phpize
$ ./configure --enable-hello
$ make

Installing is just like this:

$ make install


Testing
=======

Run the PHP script found in test directory.
